The paper focuses on developing an online evolving framework for modeling the safe autonomous vehicle control system, which involves the use of machine learning techniques to recognize unexpected situations and react appropriately. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of finite state machines, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper uses probability distributions and the Jensen-Shannon divergence method to validate the accuracy of identified transition matrices, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
